Fantasy As Teacher - Switching the I-Maker!

Forrest Knutson

Oct 31, 2025
View in app

Happy Halloween! The perfect time to talk about Fantasy and Sci-fi, and this wonderful ability to switch up your own I-maker!

Ahamkra the I-maker is the gravity of identity, the center of seriousness around who we think we are.

Aham means I
Kra means maker or doer.

It is the mechanism by which consciousness identifies with the left brains story: memory, narration, and the hallucination of continuity we call my life. Its the author and actor of the inner drama the one who clings to pleasure and avoids pain, believing the story to be real.

Through meditation, we gradually shift that center of gravity from the left brain (the storyteller) to the Right Brain (the Expanse). That shift is what creates true freedom.

Every time we enter a great story whether a fantasy novel or a sci-fi epic we practice a gentle form of disidentification. We step into the heros shoes, loosening the grip of our own narrative. For a moment, we are free from our story.

Fantasy teaches us to wear the mask lightly. Meditation teaches us to look behind the mask.

On this night of masks and imagination, remember: the self is also a costume woven of memory, stitched by thought, animated by attention. We simply learn to peer past the mask, until only Awareness remains.

Blissings!
